808.answer:
JSON.stringify throws on circular references. Replace with a custom serializer using a WeakSet to track seen objects and emit a sentinel instead of recursing:

```js
function safeStringify(value, indent = 0) {
  const seen = new WeakSet();
  return JSON.stringify(value, function (key, val) {
    if (typeof val === 'object' && val !== null) {
      if (seen.has(val)) return '[Circular]';
      seen.add(val);
    }
    return val;
  }, indent);
}

const a = { x: 1 };
a.self = a;
safeStringify(a); // '{"x":1,"self":"[Circular]"}'

const arr = [1, 2];
arr.push(arr);
safeStringify(arr); // '[1,2,"[Circular]"]'
```
The WeakSet approach works for objects and arrays. Primitives (strings, numbers) are never circular. The sentinel `'[Circular]'` is a string; deserializing will not restore the cycle, which is expected since JSON cannot represent cycles.

