public static Properties loadProperties(String filePath) throws IOException {
    Properties props = new Properties();
    try (InputStream is = new FileInputStream(filePath)) {
        props.load(is); // throws IllegalArgumentException on malformed \uXXXX
    } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {
        throw new IOException("Malformed Unicode escape in properties file: " + filePath + " — " + e.getMessage(), e);
    }
    return props;
}

Properties.load() throws IllegalArgumentException (not IOException) when it encounters a malformed Unicode escape like '\uGGGG'. Wrap it as IOException so callers can handle all file-loading errors uniformly. Always use try-with-resources for the InputStream to ensure it closes even on exceptions.

