public static String readBodyAsUtf8(HttpServletRequest request, int maxBytes) throws IOException {
    byte[] buffer = new byte[maxBytes + 1];
    try (InputStream is = request.getInputStream()) {
        int totalRead = 0, bytesRead;
        while (totalRead <= maxBytes && (bytesRead = is.read(buffer, totalRead, buffer.length - totalRead)) != -1) {
            totalRead += bytesRead;
        }
        if (totalRead > maxBytes) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Request body exceeds limit of " + maxBytes + " bytes");
        }
        return new String(buffer, 0, totalRead, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
    }
}

Reads up to maxBytes+1 to detect overflow. Throws if exceeded. Uses StandardCharsets.UTF_8 (never the default platform charset).

