public ObjectNode loadJsonFile(String path) {
    ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
    try {
        return (ObjectNode) mapper.readTree(new File(path));
    } catch (FileNotFoundException e) {
        return mapper.createObjectNode();
    } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {
        logger.error("Invalid JSON in {}: {}", path, e.getMessage());
        return mapper.createObjectNode();
    } catch (IOException e) {
        logger.error("Cannot read {}: {}", path, e.getMessage());
        return mapper.createObjectNode();
    }
}

Returns an empty ObjectNode (never null) on any failure. Distinguishes missing file from malformed JSON from other IO errors for appropriate logging. The cast to ObjectNode throws ClassCastException if root is an array — handle separately if needed.

